Ghana Says Olympic Committee Has Lifted Ban, Joy FM Reports

-- B y   E k o w   D o n t o h
-- 
2011-08-26T10:35:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-26/ghana-says-olympic-committee-has-lifted-ban-joy-fm-reports.html
A ban placed on  Ghana  by the
 International Olympic Committee  has been lifted, Joy FM  reported 
today, citing Kojo Bonsu, board chairman of the  Ghana  Sports
Council.  The decision was made after a meeting in  Seoul , Bonsu was
quoted by the Accra-based broadcaster as saying. The West
African nation was suspended in January due to political
interference in the administration of the Ghana Olympic
Committee, Joy FM reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ekow Dontoh in Accra at 
 edontoh@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Emily Bowers  at   ebowers1@bloomberg.net . 